# Endurance Have you ever started out in a game full of pep and then suddenly given out? Of course, you have to be in training if you want to carry on to the end of a hard game but, apart from this, there are certain kinds of food that will give you endurance. They stay with you longer than the foods that give you pep.
The foods that help you to "stick it out" are butter, margarine, cream, cooking oils, cheese, eggs, bacon, other meats and nuts.

Get up early enough so that you will have time to enjoy a good breakfast—eggs or cereal and milk (or both), plus toast, a strip or two of bacon, an orange or grapefruit and a glass of milk. This kind of breakfast gives you endurance for a full morning's work.
Foods That Give You Slaying Power
* butter * margarine * cream * cheese * eggs * bacon or other meats * nuts
